def: The natural process of formation or assimilation, performed bythe living organs in animals and vegetables, by which a crudesubstance is changed into something of a higher order; as, theelaboration of food into chyme; the elaboration of chyle, or sap, ortissues.
The act of praising unduly; excessive praise. Milton.
The act of reducing to any state, as of mixing two bodiescombletely. [Obs.] Bacon.
Separated at the joints; disconnected; incoherent.-- Dis*joint"ed*ly, adv.-- Dis*joint"ed*ness, n.
A species of figwort or Scrophularia (S. vernalis), and otherspecies of the same genus, mostly perennials with inconspicuouscoarse flowers.
To surrender or transfer, as an army or a fortress, on certainconditions. [R.]
The state or quality of being irreligious; ungodliness.
A kind of checked cotton or silk handkerchief.
imp. & p. p. of Plight, to pledge. Chaucer.
